stormy /ˈstɔːmɪ/

1. ADJ If there is stormy weather, there are strong winds and heavy rain. 有暴风雨的 

例： It had been a night of stormy weather, with torrential rain and high winds. 这是一个暴风雨之夜，下着倾盆大雨，刮着强风。 

2. ADJ Stormy seas have very large strong waves because there are strong winds. 巨浪滔天的 

例： They make the treacherous journey across stormy seas. 他们穿越巨浪滔天的大海进行这次危险的旅行。 

3. ADJ If you describe a situation as stormy , you mean it involves a lot of angry argument or criticism. 群情激愤的 

例： The letter was read at a stormy meeting. 这封信是在一次群情激愤的会上读的。

